[68.949657, "i", "cat > SOLUTION.txt << 'EOF'\nFIREWALL FIX SUMMARY\n====================\n\nPROBLEM:\nTraffic from ML inference service (10.200.0.0/16) to model registry (10.100.0.42:5000)\nwas timing out despite having a firewall rule that appeared correct.\n\nROOT CAUSE:\n1. The ACCEPT rule was in the INPUT chain instead of FORWARD chain\n   - INPUT chain: for traffic destined TO the gateway itself\n   - FORWARD chain: for traffic being ROUTED THROUGH the gateway\n   \n2. There was a DROP rule blocking all traffic from 10.200.0.0/16 to 10.100.0.0/16\n   that was being evaluated before any specific ACCEPT rules\n\nSOLUTION:\nMoved the ACCEPT rule from INPUT to FORWARD chain and positioned it BEFORE\nthe broader DROP rule:\n\nLine 19: iptables -A FORWARD -s 10.200.0.0/16 -d 10.100.0.42 -p tcp --dport 5000 -j ACCEPT\n\nThis allows traffic to the registry (10.100.0.42:5000) while still blocking\nother traffic from the inference subnet to the registry subnet.\n\nRULE EVALUATION ORDER:\n1. ESTABLISHED,RELATED connections (line 13)\n2. NEW connection to reg"]
[68.949762, "i", "istry:5000 - ACCEPT (line 19) ✓\n3. Other traffic to 10.100.0.0/16 - LOG and DROP (lines 25-26)\n4. General forwarding eth1->eth2 - ACCEPT (line 29)\nEOF\n"]
[68.949813, "o", "cat > SOLUTION.txt << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
